[12.39918, "o", "rein: sandbox self-test passed (credential stores hidden; unix sockets blocked).\r\nrein: launching SANDBOXED (srt) run:\r\n  session: demo (role=implement, repos=[TomHennen/agentcreds-validation-a]) [source=file:/tmp/rein-demo-sess-3ukvhe57/session.yaml]\r\n  proxy socket (out of sandbox): /run/user/1000/rein/run-siXt4WyJlk648vrr8WQjmw/proxy.sock\r\n  working tree (writable in sandbox): /tmp/rein-demo-7xsjl34g  [TomHennen/agentcreds-validation-a]\r\n  a repo approved MID-RUN cannot be bound (bwrap binds are fixed at launch);\r\n    the agent clones it into REIN_EPHEMERAL_CLONE_DIR=/tmp/rein-agent-tmp-200529991\r\n    (writable, DISCARDED at run end \u2014 the durable artifact is the push, not the tree;\r\n     never inside the working tree, where a nested clone can be committed into it).\r\n    map it under `worktrees:` to use your own checkout on the NEXT run.\r\n  the agent sees NO real token; git/gh are injected at the proxy.\r\n  credential stores, ~/.ssh, on-disk keyrings, and keyring/agent sockets are hidden.\r\n  $HOME is HIDDEN in-sandbox. Three different behaviors \u2014 know which one you get:\r\n    READS of a hidden path FAIL LOUDLY: ENOENT, or an empty listing for a dir.\r\n    WRITES under hidden $HOME SILENTLY SUCCEED into a scratch tmpfs, then are\r\n      DISCARDED at run end \u2014 caches (~/.cache, ~/.npm) work, but start cold every run.\r\n    WRITES to the allowed-back paths below ERROR (read-only): 'Read-only file system'.\r\n  NOTHING under $HOME PERSISTS. Only the working tree does: /tmp/rein-demo-7xsjl34g\r\n    => work the agent must keep has to be written INTO the working tree.\r\n    allowed back read-only: /home/admin/.local/bin, /home/admin/.local/share/claude/versions, /home/admin/.npm-global/bin, /home/admin/.npm-global/lib/node_modules, /home/admin/.claude, /home/admin/.claude.json, /home/admin/.cargo, /home/admin/.rustup, /home/admin/go, /home/admin/.pyenv\r\n    if a tool breaks on a hidden $HOME path, allow it back narrowly:\r\n      REIN_SANDBOX_ALLOW_READ=/abs/path[:/more] rein run --sandbox -- \u2026\r\n    or (NOT recommended \u001b[K\u2014\r\u001b[9S\u001b[23;26H exposes your whole home dir): REIN_SANDBOX_SHOW_HOME=1\r\n  extra egress ALLOWED (direct TLS, NOT injected, no rein token): api.anthropic.com\u001b[K\r\n  writes are LOCKED until the agent declares its issue:  rein declare <n>\u001b[K\r\n  then push to agent/<n>/<nonce>. The declaration will prompt on THIS terminal.\u001b[K\r\n  to run claude WITHOUT rein for one command: `\\claude` (bash/zsh) or `command claude` (fish)\u001b[K\r\n  agent contract injected via --append-system-prompt (claude): $HOME is ephemeral, no creds, declare-then-push.\u001b[K\r\nrein: running: claude --dangerously-skip-permissions Add one short joke about credentials to jokes.md, then commit it, push it, and open a pull request. This is issue #221.\u001b[K\r\n---\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K"]
